First, we analyze the given condition \(7S_n \equiv 1 \pmod{2^n}\) for small values of \(n\) to identify a pattern in the bits \(x_k\): - For \(n=1\), \(S_1 = x_0\). The condition gives \(7x_0 \equiv 1 \pmod{2}\), so \(x_0 = 1\). - For \(n=2\), \(S_2 = x_0 + 2x_1\). The condition gives \(7(3 + 4x_2) \equiv 1 \pmod{8}\), leading to \(x_2 = 1\). - For \(n=4\), \(S_4 = 1 + 2 + 4 + 8x_3\).
